WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.499 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.499 --> 00:00:03.260 align:middle line:84%
The chocolate chip cookie was
invented in the late 1930s

00:00:03.260 --> 00:00:06.590 align:middle line:84%
by Ruth Graves Wakefield while
working at the Toll House

00:00:06.590 --> 00:00:09.210 align:middle line:90%
Inn of Whitman, Massachusetts.

00:00:09.210 --> 00:00:12.210 align:middle line:84%
The recipe was first
published in 1938

00:00:12.210 --> 00:00:15.240 align:middle line:84%
under the name "Toll House
Chocolate Crunch Cookie."

00:00:15.240 --> 00:00:18.350 align:middle line:84%
There are competing stories as
to who the true inventor was,

00:00:18.350 --> 00:00:21.730 align:middle line:84%
but they all place the
invention in the Toll House.

00:00:21.730 --> 00:00:25.750 align:middle line:84%
Sadly, the Toll House Inn was
destroyed in a fire in 1984.

00:00:25.750 --> 00:00:29.050 align:middle line:84%
A refurbished version of
the original Toll House sign

00:00:29.050 --> 00:00:32.060 align:middle line:84%
still exists, along with
a historical marker.

00:00:32.060 --> 00:00:36.210 align:middle line:84%
Both are in a parking lot of
what is now a Wendy's fast food

00:00:36.210 --> 00:00:37.760 align:middle line:90%
restaurant.